      <c01 level="series" id="d1e188">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Letters</unittitle>
        </did>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e192">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Frank Harris</persname>to [ 
                  <persname>Werner Laurie</persname>]</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1911 May 18</unitdate>
            <physdesc>TLS, 2 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asserts that several articles on famous men
                  printed in 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Academy</title></bibref>should be rewritten before being
                  republished; mentions Carlyle, Renan, Emerson,
                  Rhodes, and 
                  <persname>Randolph Churchill</persname>as possible
                  subjects; can sell only English rights; comments on 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Man Shakespeare</title></bibref>, 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Women of Shakespeare</title></bibref>, and 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Life and Confessions of Oscar
                     Wilde</title></bibref>; hopes to find satisfactory publisher;
                  elicits opinion of pieces on Carlyle and Renan and
                  possible financial terms for the book.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e236">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Frank Harris</persname>to 
                  <persname>Werner Laurie</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1911 May 27</unitdate>
            <physdesc>TLS, 3 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses sales and prices of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Women of Shakespeare</title></bibref>, 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Man Shakespeare</title></bibref>, and 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Life and Confessions of Oscar
                     Wilde</title></bibref>; discusses anticipated publication of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Recollections of Famous Men</title></bibref>and 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Unpath'd Waters</title></bibref>; will cover the "coronation" for 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The New York World</title></bibref>and perhaps write a book on it.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e289">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Frank Harris</persname>to 
                  <persname>Werner Laurie</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n.y. Aug 10</unitdate>
            <physdesc>TLS, 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Refuses terms offered for English and colonial
                  rights to 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Women of Shakespeare</title></bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e311">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Frank Harris</persname>to 
                  <persname>Werner Laurie</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n.y. Aug 15</unitdate>
            <physdesc>TLS, 2 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses terms for 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Women of Shakespeare</title></bibref>; expects 
                  <persname>Arnold Bennett</persname>will write
                  approvingly about it; compares the book to 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Man Shakespeare</title></bibref>; hopes for simultaneous publication of
                  English and American editions; is going to 
                  <geogname>Stratford on Avon</geogname>to get pictures
                  of Shakespeare and 
                  <persname>Mary Fitton</persname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
